Vivo Energy, which operates under Shell brand, has leased eight more tanker trucks from Vehicle And Equipment Leasing Ltd.This brings its leased fleet to 50 in the last three years.Vivo Energy procurement manager Milkah Kahumbura said the company is leasing to manage operational costs, because it passes intermediate vehicle maintenance services to VAELL.VAELL's regional managing director, Paul Njeru, said the firm has diversified its portfolio and now offers customised solutions to suit every client's requirements and needs, and is continuously improving its services.